explanation: This solution uses two queues to implement a stack. The push operation is implemented by moving all elements from one queue to another and then adding the new element to the end of the second queue, then swapping the two queues. The pop, top, and empty operations are simply the standard queue operations. The time complexity of push is O(n) because in the worst case, we have to move all elements from one queue to another. The space complexity is O(n) because in the worst case, we have to store all elements in the queues.

